& [LedgerRows] is the first compatibility table
  + [row_001_heegner_gross_zagier_kolyvagin] is rank-one calibration corridor
    = scope: elliptic curves in compatible Heegner settings, analytic rank one or bounded rank-part statements
    = analytic_object: first derivative of L-function
    = source_object: Heegner point
    = measurement_object: Neron-Tate height through Gross-Zagier style formula
    = control_object: Kolyvagin system from Heegner-point derivatives
    = same_frame_score: high
    = first_mismatch: only mismatch is extrapolation beyond rank-one or special hypotheses
    = meaning_yield: strongest realized model of L-hand derivative data producing R-hand arithmetic direction plus upper control
  + [row_002_generalized_heegner_cycles] is higher-cycle source-measurement corridor
    = scope: special higher-dimensional or higher-codimension settings, often with auxiliary modularity and sign hypotheses
    = analytic_object: higher derivative, p-adic derivative, or refined leading term in special settings
    = source_object: generalized Heegner cycle or Chow-Heegner point/cycle
    = measurement_object: p-adic, derived, or height/regulator pairing
    = control_object: partial, separate, or conjectural depending on setting
    = same_frame_score: medium
    = first_mismatch: control object is not automatically supplied by the same source-measurement theorem
    = meaning_yield: best current formal home for "phase-corrected field" as regulator or height measurement
  + [row_003_diagonal_cycle_euler_system] is special higher-cycle source/control corridor
    = scope: diagonal cycles or triple-product style settings, not general elliptic-curve BSD
    = analytic_object: p-adic L-function or triple-product special value/derivative data
    = source_object: diagonal cycle or related cycle class
    = measurement_object: p-adic height or explicit reciprocity relation
    = control_object: Euler-system-like structure in special construction
    = same_frame_score: medium_high_for_special_scope
    = first_mismatch: translation from special motive/triple-product setting to general elliptic-curve BSD rank is not supplied
    = meaning_yield: highest revelation corridor because source, measurement, and control visibly coexist without becoming general proof
  + [row_004_higher_rank_euler_kolyvagin_stark] is control-first corridor
    = scope: p-adic representation settings satisfying higher-rank system hypotheses
    = analytic_object: leading term or determinant-style special element
    = source_object: suitable Euler/Stark system elements if constructed
    = measurement_object: determinant, Rubin lattice, regulator-like object
    = control_object: higher-rank Kolyvagin/Stark system
    = same_frame_score: conjectural_to_medium_when_system_exists
    = first_mismatch: existence of suitable source system for broad elliptic-curve BSD is not automatic
    = meaning_yield: clarifies upper-bound/control side of R-hand growth but does not alone construct rational directions
  + [row_005_iwasawa_main_conjecture] is analytic-to-Selmer control corridor
    = scope: ordinary/supersingular and modular settings where main conjecture input is available
    = analytic_object: p-adic L-function and characteristic ideal
    = source_object: usually indirect Selmer/cohomological data rather than explicit rational directions
    = measurement_object: p-adic regulator or leading-term refinement when available
    = control_object: Selmer characteristic ideal or main-conjecture control
    = same_frame_score: medium_for_upper_control
    = first_mismatch: lower source and independence still require separate construction or nonvanishing/regulator input
    = meaning_yield: useful for the "no hidden extra rank" side, weaker for the document's generator-growth language
  + [row_006_source_symbolic_l_hand_r_hand] is project-source symbolic route
    = scope: source-document conceptual model only
    = analytic_object: L-hand collapse
    = source_object: R-hand rational directions by traversal
    = measurement_object: phase correction
    = control_object: not supplied
    = same_frame_score: outside_as_proof
    = first_mismatch: no formal source object, measurement theorem, independence proof, or Selmer control
    = meaning_yield: good organizing metaphor after theorem corridors define the missing jobs

